<p><b>Abdul Latīf Pedrām</b> (<a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa">عبداللطيف پدرام</span>‎; born in 1963), Ph.D., is a politician and a Member of Parliament in <a href="/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a>. He emerged as a controversial figure in the press and political circles for campaigning for women's personal rights, a taboo subject in Afghanistan's culture.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Currently, he is the leader of the <a href="/wiki/National_Congress_Party_of_Afghanistan" title="National Congress Party of Afghanistan">National Congress Party of Afghanistan</a> and is one of the nine representatives of <a href="/wiki/Badakhshan_province" title="Badakhshan province" class="mw-redirect">Badakhshan province</a> in the lower house of <a href="/wiki/Wolesi_Jirga" title="Wolesi Jirga" class="mw-redirect">parliament</a>.</p>
<p></p>
